<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Britain-Tourism     09-02 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Britain-Tourism,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Record Number of Tourists Visit Britain in 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A record 15.4 million foreign tourists visited
Britain last year, including many more Japanese, Europeans and
North Americans, the British Tourist Authority said.
   The figure marked an 11 percent increase from 1986, and the
visitors spent $10.4 billion, the authority said Thursday.
   The authority said 1987 visits by Japanese increased 45 percent
from 1986 while those by Greeks and Italians increased 38 percent.
   North American tourists in 1987 increased by 19 percent from the
year before, said the government-funded authority.
   The tourist authority said Britain was fifth in tourism earnings
for a second consecutive year last year, after the United States,
Italy, Spain and France.
</TEXT>
