<HEAD>Angolan Army Reports Killing 153 UNITA Rebels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Angolan government soldiers killed 153
rebels in a week of fighting across six provinces, the official
Angolan News agency ANGOP reported.
   ANGOP quoted a Defense Ministry statement Thursday as saying 11
Angolan soldiers were killed, 37 wounded and two listed as missing
in the actions that began Aug. 24 and ended Tuesday.
   Rebels of UNITA, the National Union for the Total Independence
of Angola, are not participating in a cease-fire signed Aug. 22
between Angola, South Africa and Cuba formally ending hostilities
in southern Angola.
