fighting since 1975 to force the Cuban- and Soviet-backed Angolan
government to share power.
   The ANGOP report, monitored in Lisbon, said government troops
also captured five guerrillas, along with arms and ammunition, and
freed more than 100 civilians allegedly being held captive by the
rebels.
   The Defense Ministry said rebels had killed 25 civilians,
wounded 35 and kidnapped 11 others in guerrilla actions over the
same period.
