<HEAD>Debate Over Presidential Debates Continues</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The debate over presidential debates remains
unresolved.
   Campaign managers for Democrat Michael Dukakis and Republican
George Bush failed on Thursday to agree on how many face-to-face
encounters the candidates should have.
   Both sides held to positions taken earlier this week when Bush
campaign manager James A. Baker III offered two televised
presidential debates and Dukakis manager Paul Brountas pushed for
three.
   However, the Bush campaign appeared to nudge the schedule back
by a few days and pushed for an open format as opposed to sticking
to specific topics.
   Unlike the earlier meeting, which was conducted in person in
Washington, Thursday's negotiating session was on the telephone.
The two sides did agree to talk to each other again on the phone on
Tuesday.
