<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Gorilla Escapes,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gorilla Climbs Wall, Wanders Out Of Enclosure</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 200-pound gorilla made an
``impossible'' escape from its enclosure at the Kansas City Zoo by
scaling a wall, forcing the evacuation of about 200 people,
authorities said.
   The 13-year-old gorilla, named Molly, climbed the wall,
clambered onto a roof and then jumped down to walk into the ape
house entrance normally used by humans.
   At the time, there were no people nearby, said zoo Director
Ralph Waterhouse. The zoo was closed for about 1{ hours and about
200 people evacuated as workers dealt with the gorilla.
   Workers at the zoo locked the ape house doors and blocked them
with trucks and closed other openings with plywood. The gorilla was
then tranquilized.
   ``It still appears to be impossible,'' Waterhouse said about the
escape. ``She is extremely athletic.''
   Earlier in the summer she propped a skinny tree branch in the
corner of her outdoor exhibit and climbed to another brief spell of
freedom.
