<1ST_LINE>r i PM-MissingAmmunition     09-02 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Missing Ammunition,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ammunition For Olympic Event Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said today they were
investigating whether some missing bullets meant for an Olympic
shooting competition may be in the hands of terrorists.
   They said customs officials in the southern city of Pusan
unsealed a container on a ship and discovered that 400 rounds of
ammunition were missing. The Japanese-registered Trans World
Bridge, which was loaded in Britain, docked in Pusan on Thursday.
   Police said the ship sailed from Britain on Aug. 31 with 25,000
