<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0419</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Flash Flood Watch in Effect in Texas; Manhole Covers Pop in
Minnesota</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A flash flood watch was in effect today for parts of Texas in
the wake of heavy rains that caused some street flooding, while
downpours in Minnesota increased pressure in storm sewers enough to
blow manhole covers off.
   Rainfall totaled more than 2 inches across parts of Texas,
leaving standing water in Lubbock and water-covered streets in Big
Spring and Odessa. In New Mexico, heavy rain caused streams to
overflow.
   Thunderstorms drenched Ely, Minn., with 3 inches of rain in two
hours, leaving basements flooded and streets under water. Though
manhole covers popped, the waters rapidly subsided after the storm
passed.
   Showers and thunderstorms were scattered along the Gulf Coast
and parts of Georgia, Missouri, Tennessee, Kentucky, Oklahoma,
Kansas and Colorado.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
in Florida, Georgia, Alabama, the Tennessee Valley, the lower
Mississippi Valley, Oklahoma, Texas and New Mexico. Similar storms
were expected from lower Michigan and Wisconsin into Kansas.
Showers should be scattered in northern Maine and norther parts of
the upper Great Lakes.
   High temperatures were forecast to be in the 70s in the upper
Mississippi Valley, parts of the northern Plains and upper Great
Lakes, northern Maine, the central and southern Rockies, and along
parts of the California coast; in the 90s in Louisiana, Florida,
parts of Texas, and the Pacific Northwest; and upwards of 100
degrees in the desert southwest and the inland valleys of
California and Oregon. The remainder of the nation should be in the
80s.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 41 degrees
at Yellowstone, Wyo, to 90 at Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 72 cloudy; Boston 62 fair; Buffalo 61 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 70 cloudy; Cincinnati 66 fair; Cleveland 63 fair;
Detroit 64 fair; Miami 81 fair; New York 67 fair; Pittsburgh 60
fair; Portland, Maine 56 fair; Washington 65 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 56 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 80 fair; Denver 64
partly cloudy; Des Moines 67 cloudy; Indianapolis 67 fair; Kansas
City 69 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 63 fair; Nashville 70 fair;
New Orleans 78 cloudy; St. Louis 76 hazy.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 windy; Anchorage 52 fair; Las Vegas 85
fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 88 fair; Salt Lake City 67 fair;
San Diego 68 foggy; San Francisco 57 fair; Seattle 70 fair.
