<HEAD>PEN List Of Imprisoned Writers Includes Terry Anderson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A report issued today by the
international writers' group PEN lists Associated Press
correspondent Terry Anderson among more than 300 writers it says
are imprisoned worldwide.
   PEN released its Writers in Prison report at its annual congress
which ended today in the South Korean capital. PEN is an an
international association of poets, playrights, editors, essayists
