<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Drugs     09-02 0164</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Drugs,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seize Seven Tons of Hashish; Arrest 14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BENIDORM, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police seized seven tons of hashish in
the port of Barcelona and arrested 14 people in the Mediterranean
coastal province of Alicante to break up an international smuggling
ring, police said Friday.
   Police discovered the drug in a container on a ship in the port
of Barcelona, then placed the container under surveillance. Several
men later trucked the container south to this eastern city where
waiting police arrested the 14 alleged members of the ring.
   The people arrested included two Spaniards and 12 others of
British and Dutch nationality, he said.
   The largest hashish seizure was on July 24, when police
uncovered 17 tons of in a specially built vault on a cove near
Lloret del Mar, north of the northeastern Mediterranean city of
Barcelona. Six people were arrested.
   In recent years, Spain has become a major transport and
distribution entry point into Western Europe for traffickers of
hashish.
