<HEAD>Arrest Man In Death Of Woman Found In Hotel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GARDEN CITY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has been charged with the murder
of a woman whose body was discovered under a motel bed, days after
she was killed and guests continued to use the room, police said
Friday.
   Detective Sgt. Dennis Barry said Cornelius Walls, 49, of
Hempstead was arrested Thursday. With him, Barry said, was a
26-year-old woman who claimed she had been held against her will
for three days, and that Walls had raped and sodomized her.
   Walls was charged with second-degree murder in the death of Mary
DeOliviera of Elmont. Walls also faced charges of kidnapping, rape
and sodomy for the attack on the woman who was with him, Barry said.
   Her body was under a bed at the Oceanside Motel for at least
four days before a maintenance worker investigating complaints of a
foul odor found the body Monday. Police said her husband had
reported her missing.
   Barry said Walls was arrested based on information gathered at
the murder scene.
