<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ravioli Accident,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ravioli Factory Machine Swallows Man</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ravioli factory employee was pulled
into a dough-kneading machine, and rescuers had to bring the
machine to the hospital along with the man, authorities said.
   Calvin Knight of Mount Vernon was in stable condition Friday.
   Knight had disappeared completely in the six-foot-tall machine
Thursday at John's Ravioli Co., said Fire Commissioner Raymond
Kiernan.
   Kiernan said rescuers had to work for more than an hour before
Knight and the machine could be transported to New Rochelle
Hospital, where the blades used to knead the dough were removed.
   Knight underwent surgery and may regain most of the use of his
right arm, a spokeswoman at New Rochelle Hospital said.
   Henry Guanero, an employee at the factory, said Knight was
cleaning his machine at the end of the day when the accident
occurred.
   Neither factory officials nor the police were able to determine
exactly why Knight was pulled into the machine.
</TEXT>
