<1ST_LINE>r w AM-American-LuckyMerger     09-02 0102</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-American-Lucky Merger,90</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>FTC Gives Final Approval to Grocery Merger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Federal Trade Commission has given its
final approval to the merger of two major grocery chains, American
Stores Co. and Lucky Stores Inc.
   The merger received preliminary approval May 31.
   Under terms of a consent agreement, American Stores will sell
between 31 and 37 of its stores in California.
   American Stores, based in Salt Lake City, operates food and drug
stores under a variety of names, including Acme Markets, Alpha
Beta, Jewel, Star and Skaggs. Lucky, with headquarters in Dublin,
Calif., primarily operates Lucky retail food markets.
</TEXT>
