<HEAD>President Plans Nebraska, Kentucky Stops Tuesday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan will visit
Hastings College in Nebraska and address the annual convention of
the American Legion on his way back to Washington from California,
the White House announced Friday.
   Reagan, who has been vacationing in his home state since Aug.
16, planned to spend a quiet Labor Day weekend with his wife Nancy
at his 688-acre ranch north of this coastal resort city, said
spokesman B. Jay Cooper.
   On Tuesday, Cooper said, Reagan is scheduled to fly to the
Hastings campus to dedicate the Gray Center for the Communications
Arts. The center is named for Robert T. Gray, a Washington public
relations executive.
   Reagan then flies to Louisville, Ky., where he will address the
70th annual national convention of the American Legion, before
traveling on to Washington.
