<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF-NepalQuake     09-02 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF-Nepal Quake,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Seismic Station Records Tremors Twice</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two tremors were recorded Friday at a
seismic station here, aftershocks from a deadly earthquake last
month which killed more than 1,000 people in Nepal and India,
seismologists said.
   No damage or injuries were reported in the latest temblors.
   Seismologists said a tremor registering 4.8 on the Richter scale
occured at 3:45 a.m. and another, registering 5 on the Richter
scale, took place at 12:20 p.m.
   The epicentre of the tremors was in Udayapur, 35 miles north of
the India-Nepal border, the seismologists said.
   The Richter scale measures the engery released by an earthquake
according to the ground motion as recorded by seismographs. A
reading of 6 means the earthquake can cause severe damage and a
reading of 7 indicates a major earthquake.
   The earthquake Aug. 21 registered 6.5 on the Richter scale.
</TEXT>
