<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Koch-Gesture     09-02 0213</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Koch-Gesture,0221</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mayor Answers Heckler with Vulgar Gesture</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MONTICELLO, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New York City Mayor Edward I. Koch
answered a heckler with a vulgar gesture during a speech to the New
York City police union's convention.
   Koch, speaking to the Police Benevolent Association on Thursday,
was interrupted by a heckler who yelled an obscenity as Koch last
month's Tompkins Square Park riot.
   Koch responded by telling a joke. As part of the punch line, he
grabbed the crook of his right arm while lifting his right forearm.
``That's for you,'' he said to the heckler, prompting loud applause
and laughter.
   The police convention, held in upstate Monticello, initially had
given a cool reception to Koch as he spoke about the Aug. 7 riot,
which broke out as police tried to enforce a late-night curfew in
the Manhattan park.
   Dozens of protesters and passers-by lodged complaints of police
brutality, and an official investigation found that the Police
Department acted irresponsibly and several high-ranking police
officials were disciplined.
   After Koch returned to the riot issue, telling the assembly:
``We're going to call on you again in the near future. This time,
(act) within the rules.''
   ``Aw, come on _ you're taking all the fun out of it!'' one man
shouted.
</TEXT>
