<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brites     09-02 0351</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brites ,0366</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bright & Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLEN COVE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All babies are cute, and that's why Glen
Cove is canceling its Labor Day baby contest.
   Millie DeRiggi, the mayor's wife, said only 32 children
participated in last year's baby contest because many parents were
disappointed that their kids came out as losers.
   No one appreciated the Baby Booby Prize.
   The Long Island community will have a baby parade Saturday, and
all 130 children participating in the event will receive gold stars
to hang around their necks, and ice cream.
   Mrs. DeRiggi says the children should be celebrated, not rated.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Harrisburg Patriots football team
looked forward for a grand season opener Sunday night with a new
$1.38 million field and scoreboard.
   There's only one thing missing _ the stands.
   Mayor Stephen Reed said the Southern Bleacher Co. of Graham,
Texas, inadvertently shipped sections of the new bleachers to
another city. The bleachers will be picked up and shipped by air to
Harrisburg and it will take about five days to erect them, Reed
said.
   The Patriots, part of the Continental Interstate Football
League, will move their opener against the Pocono Mountaineers to
the adjacent RiverSide Stadium. The Patriots hope to move into the
Skyline Sports Complex for a Sept. 10 game against the Chambersburg
Cardinals.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Call them the mountain bike cops.
   Within a month, the Police Department hopes to have two
uniformed officers patrolling the downtown area on 18-speed
mountain bicycles.
   ``In a downtown area, (bicycles) are the fastest way to
respond,'' said Sgt. C.M. Poole, the department's downtown liaison
officer.
   The department began considering the idea after an officer
suggested a bicycle would be easier than a car to maneuver on
downtown streets and sidewalks.
   The chosen two will wear helmets and padded bicycle shorts as
long as the warm weather lasts. They will carry a gun and radio.
   With winter approaching, this is not the ideal season to
experiment with bicycles, Poole said. ``But if it works in the
winter, it will work anytime,'' he said.
</TEXT>
