<HEAD>West German Foreign Minister Feels Ill, Breaks Off Lecture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Foreign Minister Hans-Dietrich Genscher of
West Germany abruptly broke off a lecture Friday and left the hall
complaining of illness.
   After a hurried hospital examination, Genscher left Norway on
schedule aboard his West German air force plane, West German
Embassy and airport officials said.
   ``We have been informed that it is nothing serious, but it was
after all decided that he would undergo an examination at the
hospital,'' said spokesman Ivar Melbye.
