hall at the end of a two-day official visit, walked out unassisted
and was taken in a police car to State Hospital. West German
Ambassador Harald Hofmann finished reading the lecture.
   The address to the Norwegian-German Society was held in the
concert hall where the Nobel Peace Prize is awarded annually. It
opened a planned series of lectures on international issues.
   Earlier, Genscher met with Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland,
his Norwegian collegue and host Thorvald Stoltenberg, and members
of the Parliament's foreign relations committee.
