<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Train     09-02 0123</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Train,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Train Catches Fire In Tunnel, More Than 50 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SABADELL, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train caught fire in a tunnel outside
the Sabadell station in northeastern Spain and more than 50
passengers were injured, municipal police reported.
   They said rescue operations lasted nearly four hours due to
thick smoke in the 3.7-mile tunnel. The fire occurred when the
train was about 200 feet from the mouth of the tunnel, according to
the police.
   Authorities said most of the injuries were minor.
   The three-car train was carrying 100 people when fire broke out
in the first car and then spread to the second car, the authorities
said.
   The train was operating between the Catalonian towns of Molins
de Rei and Tarrasa.
</TEXT>
