reducing prospects for heightened inflationary pressures and giving
the Federal Reserve more leeway in its credit policy.
   The figures got a rousing welcome in the bond market. Prices of
long-term government bonds, which move in the opposite direction
from interest rates, climbed as much as $15 for each $1,000 in face
value.
