<HEAD>Xerox To Announce New Desktop Publishing Software</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Xerox Corp. is scheduled to release on Tuesday a
new generation of its Ventura Publisher personal computer software,
the best-selling software for desktop publishing in the IBM PC
market.
   The new software will be easier to use and more flexible and is
the first of its kind that allows several computer users who are
connected in a network to work on the same document, Xerox said
Friday.
   Dataquest Inc. estimated that Ventura Publisher had a 62 percent
share last year of the market for desktop publishing on
International Business Machines Corp.'s personal computers and
compatible machines. Dataquest estimates the desktop publishing
market will grow to $5.3 billion by 1990.
   The suggested retail price of the core product, Ventura
Publisher 2.0, is $895. A package including networking software has
a suggested retail price is $1,295. The products are developed by a
Xerox subsidiary, Ventura Software Inc. of Salinas, Calif.
