<HEAD>Irish Distillers Discusses Bid With France's Pernod</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Irish Distillers Group PLC, the target of a
hostile takeover bid, indicated Friday that France's Pernod Ricard
SA could emerge as a ``white knight'' merger partner.
   Pernod said Thursday that it raised its stake in Irish
Distillers to 2.8 percent from nearly 1 percent, about a week after
it revealed it was holding talks with Irish whiskey maker.
   A spokeswoman for Irish Distillers said discussions between the
two companies continued in Dublin on Friday and involved ``all
possibilities,'' including a possible offer.
   ``There is no timetable for the conclusion of these talks but it
will be as soon as possible,'' she said.
   Irish Distillers has been under siege from British liquor group
Grand Metropolitan PLC, which launched a hostile $359 million bid
two weeks ago.
   Grand Metropolitan has said it will not raise its offer unless a
third party enters the bidding.
